  "title": "The Doctor, the Sith, and the Presav",
  "summary": "Aboard her ship the Red Sky, the doctor Lynae Cassius completes the medical treatment that revives the ancient Sith lord Malus from his carbonite imprisonment and recommends he meet Crestian Tarasar, the Presav of the Caspian Union. Over a formal pot of tea in the crew lounge, the three engage in a long, wary, philosophical sparring match about galactic power, the Imperium under Darth Malign (formerly Tyler), its mutual-defense pact with the Caspian Union, and the looming hand of Vadim. Malus argues that the Empire and New Republic are locked in self-destructive internal conflict and offers, in exchange for discreet support and intelligence, to break the chains binding the Union to the Imperium, even hinting he could kill Vadim. Crestian, defending the Imperium as a genuine friend to a Caspar he rebuilt from genocide, treats the meeting as a job interview rather than a negotiation, while Lynae repeatedly presses Malus to reveal his true goals. News of riots on the New Republic world Chandrila prompts talk of soft-power manipulation, but the meeting ends with Lynae reserving judgment and challenging Malus to prove his intentions, after which he accepts her hospitality to freshen up.",
